response:
To enable point-in-time recovery (PITR) for a DynamoDB table in Terraform:

1. We must first identify the DynamoDB table resource in the configuration.
2. Point-in-time recovery is enabled at the table level using the `point_in_time_recovery` block.
3. This block has a single required attribute: `enabled`, which must be set to `true`.

Since PITR cannot be enabled directly on an existing unmanaged table (i.e., one not already defined in Terraform), we assume the table is defined using a `aws_dynamodb_table` resource.

We will define or update the DynamoDB table with the `point_in_time_recovery` block to turn on PITR.

```hcl
resource "aws_dynamodb_table" "example" {
  name         = "example-table"
  hash_key     = "id"
  billing_mode = "PAY_PER_REQUEST"

  attribute {
    name = "id"
    type = "S"
  }

  point_in_time_recovery {
    enabled = true
  }
}
```

